Today, I voted in favor of the Continuing Resolution to ensure our government stays open and functioning to serve the American people. 

Although a short-term measure is not ideal, this resolution gives Congress time to assemble an appropriate full-year government funding bill. @HouseGOP took action to avoid a shutdown while maintaining our commitment to fiscal discipline.

As the U.S. Senate continues to work on passing legislation to extend the funding deadline, I have requested that my pay be withheld in the event a shutdown occurs. 

Our job is to make sure the government runs efficiently and always puts the needs of the American people first. I will continue working with my colleagues until an agreement is reached.
